<TEXT>
   If there were any doubts that folks in
Fort Worth know their country music entertainers, there's none now.
   The Fort Worth Star-Telegram published a photograph of the back
pockets on a pair of tight blue jeans on Sunday.
   ``This is a shot of the most famous buns in Texas,'' said
photographer Bill Joe Gabriel, who provided the photo to the
newspaper and promised to give it to the first caller to identify
the singing star.
   Star-Telegram columnist Dave Bryant said the paper was besieged
with calls, and 800 people correctly identified the derriere as
belonging to George Strait.
