<HEAD>`Reindeer' Mistaken for Wild Doe is Shot by Hunter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AFTON, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A would-be Santa says he lost one of his
``reindeer'' to a hunter on the first day of deer season.
   One of the dozen European fallow deer at Santa's Cottage escaped
from its pen on Thanksgiving, said owner Fred Kreig.
   A hunter thought the 70-pound deer was wild and shot it, said
Kreig, who gives tours and holds holiday events at the farm 50
miles southeast of Syracuse for needy children.
   The hunter realized his mistake and offered to pay for the deer,
valued at $800.
   ``I told him the idea of his calling to apologize was plenty,''
said Kreig, who invited the hunter to bring his family to Santa's
Cottage whenever he wants.
