<SECOND>PM-Obit-Civardi,0115</SECOND>
<HEAD>Italian Cardinal Ernesto Civardi Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Italian Cardinal Ernesto Civardi has died at
the age of 83, the Vatican said today.
   Civardi, born in Fossarmato near Pavia in 1906, died Tuesday in
Rome. The cause of death was not given.
   He was consecrated as bishop in 1967 and elevated to cardinal by
Pope John Paul II in 1979. The pope will lead funeral services for
Civardi at the Vatican on Thursday.
   Civardi's death brings the number of Roman Catholic cardinals to
149. Of those, 114 are under the age of 80 and thus eligible to
participate in a conclave for the election of a new pope.
