<HEAD>New Book on Wright Says Rostenkowski Made Anti-Semitic Comment</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Wright Book</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDs: Note contents 3rd graf</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A new book on former House Speaker Jim Wright
recounts a private leadership meeting at which Rep. Dan
Rostenkowski, chairman of the Ways and Means Committee, is said to
have made an anti-Semitic comment.
   House leadership officials were considering assigning Rep.
Howard Wolpe, D-Mich., to the House Foreign Affairs Committee.
Wolpe, who is Jewish, had a background in international relations.
   But Rostenkowski, a Chicago Democrat, objected. ``You can't put
him there. There are already four kikes on that committee,'' he is
quoted as saying in the book, ``The Ambition and the Power.''
   A spokesman for Rostenkowski, Jim Jaffe, flatly denied that the
comment was made. But the book's author, John Barry, insists he had
several sources for the remark. ``I wouldn't have put something
like that in the book unless I were certain of it,'' he said.
</TEXT>
