<FIRST>r a PM-HelicopterCrash     11-29 0200</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Helicopter Crash,0209</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ski Executive Killed, Five Injured in Chopper Crash at Resort</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto SK1</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARK CITY, Utah (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A helicopter hauling equipment from a
mountain flipped over and crashed when a dangling cable snagged a
trailer, authorities said. A ski resort executive was killed and
five other people were injured.
   The pilot was critically injured and two passengers were
seriously hurt Tuesday, hospital officials said.
   The copter was clearing equipment and transporting people
following last week's World Cup races at the Park City Ski resort,
officials said.
   The helicopter had unloaded equipment and was taking off for
another run. Witnesses told police the copter's steel cable snagged
on a trailer, snapped and flew upward into the rotor, Police Chief
Frank Bell said.
   ``It came down upside down ... there was no fire and nobody on
the ground was injured,'' said Bell.
   Craig Badami, 37, of Park City, was killed. Badami was vice
president of marketing for Park City Ski Resort and director of the
World Cup competition.
   The helicopter came down near a ski lift, hurling metal
fragments 1,000 feet, Bell said. The ski run was not open for
public skiing.
   The Federal Aviation Administration is investigating.
</TEXT>
