be used by the state attorney's office to support charges against
them.
   ``I'm trying to avoid charges ever being brought against these
people,'' Booth told the judge. ``It would form a link in a chain
of evidence that the state could use. It would overwhelmingly
incriminate them.''
   The judge said Booth should have anticipated the problem.
   Amtrak contends federal law exempts the national rail passenger
line from state pollution control laws. Amtrak says it would be too
expensive to add holding tanks to the toilets aboard all its trains.
