<HEAD>Navy Helicopter Crashes Off Okinawa</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS last graf to UPDATE with names of crew.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PEARL HARBOR, Hawaii (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. Navy SH-2F Sea Sprite
helicopter crashed off Okinawa and one of the three crewmembers
aboard was missing, the Navy said Wednesday.
   The accident occurred at 3:50 p.m. HST Tuesday (10:50 a.m.
Wednesday in Japan) about 20 miles east of Buckner Bay Okinawa, the
Navy said in a statement from Pearl Harbor.
   The helicopter's base ship, the USS Oldendorf, rescued two crew
members Tuesday, the Navy said. Navy and Marine rescue aircraft
from Okinawa joined the search for the third, the Navy said.
   The USS Oldendorf is based at Yokosuka, Japan.
   The crew was conducting routine training operations when the
heliocopter crashed into the Pacific, the Navy said.
   The missing crewman was identified as Ens. Ralph A. Barile of
Ewa Beach, Hawaii, the co-pilot. Rescued were the pilot, Lt. Cmdr.
Alan R. Batterman of Chula Vista, Claif., and sensor operator,
Petty Officer 3rd Class Todd Rhode of Rocky River, Ohio.
