<FIRST>d f BC-EC-China     11-29 0132</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-EC-China,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>EC Probes Alleged Dumping Of Chinese Typewriter Ribbon Fabric</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The European Community Commission said
Wednesday that it was investigating alleged dumping by China of
silk used to make typewriter ribbon.
   The European Community's only producer of the silk, Spinnhuette
GmbH of West Germany, claimed the China National Silk Import and
Export Corp. sold the silk at artificially low prices.
   The complaint says Chinese silk imports rose to 250,000 square
meters the first nine months of 1989 from 150,000 square meters in
1986, giving that country a nearly 25 percent share of the EC's
market.
   Spinnhuette GmbH, the only company in an industrialized country
to manufacture the typewriter ribbon silk, claimed its share of the
market has dropped to 75 percent from 87 percent in 1986.
