<HEAD>Philip Morris Announces $1.5 Million Stock Buyback</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Philip Morris Cos. announced Wednesday it is
beginning a stock buyback program under which the food and tobacco
giant will repurchase $1.5 billion worth of its shares.
   Philip Morris stock closed at $41.87{, up 37{ cents a share in
New York Stock Exchange composite trading Wednesday. At that price,
the company would repurchase more than 35.8 million or 2.4 percent
of its 928 million outstanding shares.
   The company said it would purchase the shares on the open market
from time to time. It did not set a deadline for completing the
buyback.
   Many corporations periodically announce share buyback plans,
often as a defensive precaution or as a method of raising the price
of their stock.
